      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Although 2-substituted 2-cyclopentenones are in a base-catalyzed equilibrium with their 5-substituted 2-cyclopentenone isomers, the analogous isomerization is not observed for 2-substituted 2-cyclohexenones. Explain.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBajRZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--357a23e798fda94411e38958e7601e349d5d7367/OChem_22_EC_041.jpg\" alt=\"2-Methyl-2-cyclohexen-1-one reacts with base to form 6-Methyl-2-cyclohexen-1-one\">",
